content: Created `pyproject.toml` with setuptools-based packaging metadata, a `jsonschema` dependency, and a `benchmarks-validate` console script entry point wired to `benchmarks.validate:main`.

output.code:
from pathlib import Path
import json

target_path = Path('/mnt/data').joinpath('pyproject.toml')
target_path.parent.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

chunks = [
"""[build-system]
requires = ["setuptools>=69", "wheel"]
build-backend = "setuptools.build_meta"
""",
"""[project]
name = "generated_library_1766438416249"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "Minimal reference implementation for loading a benchmark JSON schema and validating benchmark runs."
readme = "README.md"
requires-python = ">=3.9"
license = {text = "MIT"}
authors = [{name = "OpenAI", email = "noreply@openai.com"}]
dependencies = [
  "jsonschema>=4.21.0",
]
keywords = ["benchmark", "jsonschema", "validation"]

[project.urls]
Repository = "https://example.invalid/generated_library_1766438416249"
""",
"""[project.scripts]
benchmarks-validate = "benchmarks.validate:main"
""",
"""[tool.setuptools]
package-dir = {"" = "src"}

[tool.setuptools.packages.find]
where = ["src"]
""",
]

final_text = '\n'.join(block.strip('\n') for block in chunks).strip() + '\n'
target_path.write_text(final_text, encoding='utf-8')

print('FILE_WRITTEN:pyproject.toml')
print('DIR_STATE:' + json.dumps(sorted(str(p.relative_to(Path("/mnt/data"))) for p in target_path.parent.glob('*') if p.is_file())))
